quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
67,1,"Blessed is He {1} in Whose Hand is the dominion of the Universe, {2} and Who has power over everything; {3}",footnotes:1:Tabaraka is a superlative from barkat. Barkat comprehends the meanings of exaltation and greatness
67,2,"Who created death and life that He might try you as to which of you is better in deed. {1} He is the Most Mighty, the Most Forgiving; {2}",footnotes:1:That is
67,3,"Who created the seven heavens one upon another. {1} You will see no incongruity in the Merciful One's creation. {2} Turn your vision again, can you see any flaw? {3}",footnotes:1:For explanation
67,4,"Then turn your vision again, and then again; in the end your vision will come back to you, worn out and frustrated."
67,5,"We have adorned the lower heaven {1} with lamps, {2} and have made them a means to drive away the satans. {3} We have prepared for them the chastisement of the Blazing Fire.",footnotes:1:The word masabih in the original has been used as a common noun
67,6,"The chastisement of Hell awaits those who disbelieve in their Lord. {1} What a wretched destination!",footnotes:1:That is
67,7,"When they will be cast into it, they will hear it roar as it boils, {1}",footnotes:1:The word shahiq is used for producing a cry like the donkey’s braying. The sentence may also mean that it could be the sound of Hell itself
67,8,"as though it will burst with rage. Every time a multitude is cast into it, its keepers will ask them: “Did no warner come to you?” {1}",footnotes:1:The real nature of this question will not be of a question that the keepers of Hell would like to ask them whether a warner from Allah had come to them or not
67,9,"They will say: “Yes, a warner came to us, but we gave the lie to him and said: 'Allah has revealed nothing. You are surely in huge error.' {1}",footnotes:1:That is
67,10,"They will say: 'If we had only listened and understood, {1} we would not be among the inmates of the Blazing Fire.'”",footnotes:1:If we had listened or understood: If we had listened to the Prophets with attention as seekers after truth or used our intellect to understand what actually was the message they were presenting before us. Here listening has been given priority over understanding
67,11,"Thus will they confess their sins. {1} Damned are these inmates of the Blazing Fire.",footnotes:1:The word dhanb (sin) has been used in the singular. It means that the real sin because of which they became worthy of Hell was to belie the Messengers and refuse to obey them. All other sins are its consequences.
67,12,"Surely forgiveness and a mighty reward {1} await those who fear Allah without seeing Him. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
